abstract.text: MapsIndoors enables you to show indoor maps in your apps.
MapsIndoors iOS SDK v4 can use either Google Maps or Mapbox Maps to show and interact with your indoors maps in an iOS app.
MapsIndoors iOS SDK needs to be initialised with a MapsIndoors API Key which is used to load the map data into your app.

abstract.text: MapsIndoors uses DisplayRules to define how everything is shown on the map. DisplayRules are defined in the MapsIndoors CMS but you may want to make temporary changes while showing the map.

MPBookingService allows for access to the MapsIndoors booking service.
The booking service is a special integration that has to be enabled in the MapsIndoors cloud systems.
